title: Vet who performs life-saving operations on big cats
text: show ad Is this America's bravest surgeon? Vet who specializes in big cats performs life-saving operations on rescued lions, tigers and cougars Dr Justin Boorstein started as a volunteer at the Big Cat Rescue sanctuary in Tampa, Florida, ten years ago He admits job can be 'dangerous', but says operations are almost 'identical' to those performed on small cats His most memorable cases have involved a tiger's penis and a lynx with strange eating habits Published: 13:05 GMT, 24 February 2017 | Updated: 14:13 GMT, 24 February 2017 6 shares
